ame, typically the son of a father with the same name."]}]},{"name":"Kyburg","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Helmut.","Swiss German: probably a variant of the personal name <i>Tiburtius</i>."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Hartmann","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["from <i>hard</i> ‘strong, hardy’ + <i>man</i> ‘man’. The Blessed Hartmann (  d. 1164 ) enjoyed a cult in Austria.  Hartmann von Aue  (  <i>c.</i>1170– <i>c.</i>1220 ) was an influential writer of chivalric romances."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Graf Hartmann V von Kyburg was born about 1227, in Württemberg, Germany, his father, Werner I von Kyburg, was 38 and his mother, Berthe von Lothringen, was 24. He married Élisabeth de Bourgogne on 27 January 1254. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died on 3 September 1263, in Kyburg, Zürich, Switzerland, at the age of 37, and was buried in Wettingen, Aargau, Switzerland."},"et":{"environ 1227–3 September 1263":"umbes 1227–3. september 1263","1222–1269":"1222–1269","1227–1263":"1227–1263","1240–1275":"1240–1275","1256–1283":"1256–1283","1190–1228":"1190–1228","1204–1242":"1204–1242","1190":"1190","1242":"1242","1275":"1275","1263":"1263","1240":"1240","1283":"1283","3 September 1263":"3. september 1263","6 December 1242":"6. detsember 1242","1228":"1228","1227":"1227","1204":"1204","1269":"1269","27 January 1254":"27. jaanuar 1254","1256":"1256","1222":"1222","environ 1227":"umbes 1227","Wettingen":"Wettingen, Aargau, Šveits","Kyburg, Zürich, Zwitserland":"Kyburg, Zürich, Šveits","Kyburg, Zürich, Switzerland":"Kyburg, Zürich, Šveits","Schalksburg, Schwarzwaldkreis, Württemberg, Allemagne":"Württemberg, Saksamaa","Palestine":"Palestiina","Clairlieu, Aube, Champagne-Ardenne, France":"Clairlieu, Aube, Champagne-Ardenne, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"environ 122